# Register–Dispose Pairing

When you register something (camera, event handler, provider reference), think about what happens when it is removed. Every registration needs a matching unregistration or cleanup.

## Rule

- **Register** in `Initialize` or constructor → **Unregister** in `Dispose`
- If a component registers with a shared registry/provider, it must unregister when disposed
- Do not leave registrations orphaned when scopes or objects are destroyed

## Example

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD – camera registered on init, unregistered on dispose
public void Initialize()
{
    _cameraStack.Register(_view.Camera);
}

public void Dispose()
{
    _cameraStack.Unregister(_view.Camera);
}
```

```csharp
// ❌ BAD – registers but never unregisters; camera stays in stack after view layer is destroyed
public void Initialize()
{
    _cameraStack.Register(_view.Camera);
}
```

## Rationale

- Prevents stale references and leaks
- Keeps shared state (registries, stacks, providers) consistent with actual lifecycle
